catalog.description: Rigorous, in-depth coverage of the structure and function of the human body. Gross and microscopic anatomy of all major organ systems with their associated organs and tissues. Fundamental physiology concepts in each system are also introduced. Lab instruction includes prosected human cadavers.
catalog.note: Pre-professional students should consult the advisement center when choosing between PDBIO 220 and PDBIO 210 as some programs require 4 credits of anatomy.
catalog.title: Human Anatomy (with lab).

course_headers.header_text: PDBIO 220: Pre-professional students should consult with the advisement center when choosing between PDBio 210 and PDBio 220 since some programs require 4 credit hours of Anatomy.
